>%W<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":24:{s:2:"ID";i:23100;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-04-23 04:42:09";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-23 04:42:09";s:12:"post_content";s:4418:"<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #87a629;"><strong> Day 1</strong></span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong><span style="color: #de6d0b;">Welcome to Costa Rica!!!</span> <span style="color: #808080;">Private or shared air-conditioned transportation from international airport in San Jose to Hotel los Lagos, </span></strong></span><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>2 nights’ accommodations  in double standard room with daily breakfast included.</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>The rooms are fully equipped featuring roomy private bath, hot water, hair dryer ,air conditioning, cable tv,mini-fridge,safety box,electronic clocks  and of course ,a spectacular view of the arenal volcano.</strong></span></p>

<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #87a629;"><strong>Day 2</strong></span></h3>
<span style="color: #de6d0b;"><strong>Morning: Horseback Riding </strong></span>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Departure time: 08:30 am, after breakfast</strong></span>. <span style="color: #808080;"><strong>The tour goes through the hotel’s hacienda until Los Juncos Lake and passes on to the observatory where, on a clear day, you can appreciate the great view of the Arenal Volcano. W</strong><strong>e stay for a while in the Arenal Volcano scenic point. </strong></span></p>
<span style="color: #de6d0b;"><strong>Afternoon: Zipline </strong></span>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>The canopy route consists of 12 cables and 13 platforms, covering a full distance of 2.8 kilometers (1.7 miles), which makes this the longest and most memorable tour of its kind in the area. The cables' lengths vary from 50 meters to 500 meters, with different heights and speeds.</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Don't forget that after an intense and active adventure day you can relax in the hotel’s natural hot springs and take your dinner.</strong></span></p>

<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #87a629;"><strong>Day 3</strong></span></h3>
<span style="color: #de6d0b;"><strong>Transportation from  Los Lagos Hotel to  hotel San Bada in Manuel Antonio </strong></span>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>3 nights’ accommodations at hotel san bada Manuel Antonio national park &amp; beach in standard room. </strong><strong>Hotel San Bada is located next to the World Famous Manuel Antonio National Park in Costa Rica, and close to Quepos Town</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Standard room are beautifully decorated, air conditioned room with two full size beds, large bathroom with shower, hairdryer, iron and iron board (upon request), wardrobe, cable tv, telephone, safety deposit box, alarm radio with clock, mini fridge and furnished balcony. The room offers a view of the rainforest on the edge of Manuel Antonio National Park.</strong></span></p>

<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #87a629;"><strong>Day 4</strong></span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #de6d0b;"><strong>Free Day, This day is yours to relax and enjoy Manuel Antonio beach</strong></span></p>

<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #87a629;"><strong>Day 5</strong></span></h3>
<span style="color: #de6d0b;"><strong>Sunset Sail and Snorkel Tour</strong></span>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Come aboard in search of spotted dolphins, migrating humpback whales, sea turtles and manta rays.  As we make our way down the coastline of Manuel Antonio National Park, the mysterious islands, jagged cliffs and unique rock formations will look almost close enough to reach out and touch. These are the nesting grounds and home for numerous species of marine birds, including pelicans, boobies and ibises, and that is before we’ve started snorkeling.</strong></span></p>

<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #87a629;"><strong>Day 6</strong></span></h3>
<span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Transportation from manuel Antonio to  Juan Santamaria Airport </strong></span>

